59.6	Paul_Buchheit	Paul Buchheit	Paul Buchheit is an American computer programmer and entrepreneur. He was the creator and lead developer of Gmail. He developed the original prototype of Google AdSense as part of his work on Gmail. He also suggested the company's now-famous motto "Don't be evil" in a 2000 meeting on company values. The motto was originally coined in 1999 by Amit Patel, one of Google's first engineers, in a collaborative resistance against the company's hiring policies.	
